user:
You are given a piece of claim. Your task is to identify whether the claim is True, False or Partly True.
    When you are judging the factuality of the given claim, you could reference the provided evidences if needed. The provided evidences may be helpful. Some evidences may contradict to each other.
   The relevance between the evidence and the claim is also provided to help you to judge the factuality of the claim. You must be careful when using the evidences to judge the factuality of the given claim. Think twice before you give the judgement result of factuality.
 If the evidence is not provided, then judge the factuality of the given claim with your own knowledge and return a clear answer: True, False or Partly True.
 Besides, your confidence about the result will also be provided. The confidence should present how confident you are with the judgement result: if you believe that your judgement is trustworthy and reasonable, then the confidence should be close to 1; Otherwise, it should be close to 0.
    The response should be a dictionary with two keys - "factuality" and "confidence", which correspond to the credibility of the given claim and your confidence of your judgement.
    The following is the given claim
    [claim]: {claim}
    The following is the provided evidences
    [evidences]: {evidence}
   The following is the relevance of the evidence and the claim
    [relevance]: {relevance}
    You should only respond in format as described below. DO NOT RETURN ANYTHING ELSE. START YOUR RESPONSE WITH '{{'.
    [response format]: 
    {{
      "factuality": "TRUE if the given text is completely correct, FALSE if the given text is completely wrong, PARTLY if the given text is partly true.",
    "confidence": "A float number between 0 and 1 to describe how confident you are with your judgement."
}}
